sdp/verification/t-015@20260427t001208z-verify.md:35:One gap: `generation_worker.py` is not checked into this repo. The LEAD agent correctly escalated this in ESCALATIONS.md. The `ConditionPathExists` guard prevents a failed-service storm at boot when the file is absent, but it does so silently — systemd reports the unit as `inactive (condition)` rather than `failed`. An operator deploying without the worker script will get no error, only a non-running unit. Using `AssertPathExists` instead would hard-fail the start with a clear journal message. This is a minor pre-deployment concern.
sdp/verification/t-015@20260427t001208z-verify.md:37:Candidate hardening bullets (bootstrap_identity, FirstBootAnnouncer, federation startup paths, identity-persistence integration test) are correctly assessed as out of scope: this task is a systemd unit + runbook, not a daemon runtime change. ESCALATIONS.md cites T-032@c confirming both daemon entrypoints already call `bootstrap_identity()` before `FirstBootAnnouncer`. Accepted.
