# Changelog

## Unreleased

- Added depth-2 voice alias report helpers (frac-0032): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/voice_aliases.py` now exposes frozen `VoiceAliasEntry` and `VoiceAliasReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `voice_namespace`, `voice_alias_family`, `is_aliased_voice`, `iter_alias_pairs`, `aliases_for_target`, `alias_chain`, `build_voice_alias_entry`, `build_voice_alias_report`, and `summarize_voice_alias_report` so runtime/operator diagnostics can resolve the existing eleven-entry `RUNTIME_VOICE_ALIAS` table into a JSON-safe summary with ordered source/target voices, namespace counts (core vs senseweave), family counts (struck_tonal, metallic, granular, drum, other), senseweave-variant and core-alias counts, unique-target count, target-to-sources mapping, and per-alias entries flagging `is_senseweave_variant` and `is_changed`. Existing `resolve_runtime_voice_name` lookup behavior remains unchanged; `tests/test_voice_aliases_depth.py` pins helper outputs, frozen entry/report shape, JSON-safe summary stability, agreement with `resolve_runtime_voice_name`, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_voice_aliases.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.

- Added depth-2 synthesis architecture registry report helpers (frac-0031): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis_architecture_registry.py` now exposes frozen `ArchitectureProfile` and `ArchitectureRegistryReport` dataclasses plus pure helpers `affinity_band`, `control_span_band`, `fallback_chain`, `build_architecture_profile`, `build_architecture_registry_report`, and `summarize_architecture_registry_report` so planner/operator diagnostics can resolve the existing six-family synthesis strategy registry into a JSON-safe summary with ordered architecture IDs, phase winners, phase-ranked candidates, role-to-architecture mappings, fallback chains, macro-control defaults/span bands, high-affinity phase bands, missing coverage diagnostics, and per-architecture profiles. Existing registry entries and lookup behavior remain unchanged; `tests/test_synthesis_architecture_registry_depth.py` pins helper cutpoints, fallback-cycle handling, profile/report shape, JSON-safe summary stability, agreement with existing lookup helpers, and fractal depth >= 2, while `tests/test_synthesis_architecture_registry.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.

